-- China shares close nearly flat after property data, earnings
-- 
-- Fri Apr 18, 2014 03:12AM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, April 18 (Reuters) - China shares closed nearly flat on Friday, with property stocks limiting the market's momentum after data showed Chinese home price rises had slowed further in March.

The Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> ended down 0.05 percent at 2,097.75 points. The CSI300 <.CSI300> of the leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings closed flat. On the week, the SSEC index closed down 1.4 percent. Average new home prices in China's 70 major cities rose 7.7 percent in March from a year earlier, easing from the previous month's 8.7 percent rise, according to Reuters calculations based on official data. [ID:nL3N0NA0BF] China Fortune Land Co Ltd <600340.SS> fell 3.5 percent and Ningbo Fuda Co Ltd <600724.SS> dropped 2.4 percent. Great Wall Motor Co Ltd <601633.SS> slid 5.5 percent, becoming the day's biggest loser on both indexes, after the company posted a sharp slowdown in first-quarter earnings growth.[ID:nWNBS00FBS] But ZTE Corp <000063.SZ>, China's second-biggest maker of telecommunications equipment, gained 0.8 percent after the company reported a tripling of net profit in the first quarter. [ID:nL3N0N310B]